      <div class="summary">
        <h2><a href="http://screenprism.dev/insights/article/was-it-necessary-for-birdman-to-be-filmed-to-look-like-one-continuous-take">Did they need to make &#8220;Birdman&#8221; look like one continuous take</a></h2>
        <p>"Birdman" is shot to look like one long continuous take without camera cuts.  Unbroken takes often bring a film closer to live theater and, in this case, parallel the story.</p>
